For writing Kivy codes write install below packages as per python version:-

For Python 3.9:
python -m pip install kivy[base] kivy_examples
python -m pip install pygame

For Python 3.7 and lower:
python -m pip install --upgrade pip wheel setuptools
python -m pip install docutils pygments pypiwin32 kivy.deps.sdl2 kivy.deps.glew
python -m pip install kivy.deps.gstreamer
python -m pip install kivy.deps.angle
python -m pip install pygame
python -m pip install kivy

For Python 3.8:
pip install kivy[base] kivy_examples --pre --extra-index-url https://kivy.org/downloads/simple/

python -m pip install pygame

=====================================================================================================================

For debuging and installing the app on phone use below steps(it can be used only on ubuntu):-

Phone setting:-
	(1) Connect the phone to laptop
	(2) Open setting -> about phone -> software info -> build number(tap 7 times.. will enable developer mode on phone)
	(3) go to developer options -> start awake(enable) && usb debugging (enabled)


Install Ubuntu


(1)sudo apt install git
	(i)  git clone https://github.com/kivy/buildozer.git
	(ii) git clone https://github.com/ranamitabh/kivyHelloWorld.git


(2) sudo apt-get install python3.7
(3) sudo apt-get install python3-setuptools
(4) python3 setup.py install
(2) buildozer init
(3) sudo apt update
(4) sudo apt install -y git zip openjdk-8-jdk python3-pip autoconf libtool pkg-config zlib1g-dev libncurses5-dev libncursesw5-dev libtinfo5 cmake libffi-dev
(5) pip3 install --user --upgrade cython virtualenv
(6) sudo apt-get install cython
(7) buildozer android debug deploy run